# 🚁 Tiny Object Detection in Aerial Images

A deep learning-based Computer Vision project focused on detecting **small objects** (vehicles, pedestrians) in aerial imagery using YOLOv8. This project improves detection performance using **image tiling techniques** and provides a **dark-themed interactive UI**.

---

## 📌 Problem Statement

Detecting small objects in aerial images is challenging due to:
- Low resolution of objects
- Large scene coverage
- Dense object distribution

Traditional object detection models often fail to accurately detect tiny objects.

---

## 🎯 Objective

- Build an object detection model for aerial images
- Improve detection of small objects
- Deploy an interactive UI for real-time predictions

---

## 🧠 Approach

### 🔹 Model
- YOLOv8 (Ultralytics)

### 🔹 Dataset
- VisDrone Dataset (Aerial imagery)

### 🔹 Key Techniques
- Image tiling to enhance small object visibility
- Data preprocessing and annotation conversion
- Model training and evaluation using mAP

---

## 🔥 Key Features

✔ Tiny object detection using YOLOv8  
✔ Image tiling for improved performance  
✔ Dark-themed interactive UI (Gradio)  
✔ Deployed on Hugging Face Spaces  

---

## 🧪 Results

| Method            | Performance |
|------------------|------------|
| Standard YOLOv8  | Misses small objects |
| With Tiling      | Improved detection accuracy |

